<topic id='class_consultant.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>Class: CONSULTANT - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
    <p>
A subtype of 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_care_professional">CARE PROFESSIONAL</xref>.        </p>
    <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_person">PERSON</xref>
 contracted by a 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_health_care_provider">Health Care Provider</xref>
 who has been appointed by a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_consultant">CONSULTANT</xref>'s appointment committee.        </p>
    <p>
He or she must be a member of a Royal College or Faculty. This includes 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_general_practitioner">GENERAL PRACTITIONERS</xref>
 in cases where a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_general_practitioner">GENERAL PRACTITIONER</xref>
 is responsible for 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 care and has an arrangement with the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_health_care_provider">Health Care Provider</xref>.        </p>
    <p>
The 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_main_specialty">MAIN SPECIALTY</xref>
 of a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_general_practitioner">GENERAL PRACTITIONER</xref>
 will always be General Medical Practice or General Dental Practice. For diagnostic departments, this includes a non-medical scientist of equivalent standing (to a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_consultant">CONSULTANT</xref>).        </p>
  </div>
